 716:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   * @note   When WRP is active in a zone, it cannot be erased or programmed.
 717:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   *         Consequently, a software mass erase cannot be performed if one zone
 718:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   *         is write-protected.
 719:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   * @note   When the memory read protection level is selected (RDP level = 1),
 720:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   *         it is not possible to program or erase Flash memory if the CPU debug
 721:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   *         features are connected (JTAG or single wire) or boot code is being
 722:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   *         executed from RAM or System flash, even if WRP is not activated.
 723:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   * @note   To configure the WRP options, the option lock bit OPTLOCK must be
 724:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   *         cleared with the call of the @ref HAL_FLASH_OB_Unlock() function.
 725:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_flash_ex.c ****   * @note   To validate the WRP options, the option bytes must be reloaded
